              <tr>
                <td bgcolor="#ECECEC" valign="top"
 nowrap><b><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2">UsulDaNeriak</font></b></td>
                <td bgcolor="#ECECEC" valign="top"><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;07/29/2003&nbsp;: 02:37:03 AM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> hope that helps:<br /><br />Completing the Coldain Military Wristguard quest in 30-40 mins:<br /><br />(If you are not familiar with the zones, get maps from eqatlas.com because I'm not going to take the time to give the exact loc's of all these places). To do the quest you need to have at least apprehensive faction to both Giants and Coldain. So the way around faction issues to create a new character that worships Rallos Zek. Contrary to information on some sites, you can completely skip the initial part of the quest dealing with killing wolfs and getting the harness. Follow these steps below and you will have the bracer in under an hour.<br /><br />Step Number 1: With your Main Character, purchase 3 vendor sold invisible potions (they cost 10pp apiece). If you have the money and don't want the hassle of asking others for SoW, buy a stack of SoW potions as well. Place these potions in your shared bank account. Now run your main character to the Crystal Caverns and log out.<br /><br />Step Number 2: Create a Halfling Warrior (needs to be a short race) and chose Rallos Zek as your god. Click the PoK book. Go to the soul binder in PoK and bind yourself. Grab your potions out of the bank and head to the Great Divide book.<br /><br />Step Number 3: You won't have to worry about mobs in Great Divide killing you, so just run over to the Eastern Wastes zone. Once in EW, avoid every mob you see and make your way to the Rygorr Fort. If there are people outside killing the guards, you will be able to zone into Crystal Caverns. If not, gulp an invis potion and zone in.<br /><br />Step Number 4: Log your Main Character in and start killing every orc you see. It has never taken me more than 10 mins to get a Bottle of Karsin Acid to drop. Once one does drop. Log out, relog the Halfling warrior, loot the bottle, and suicide on the nearest mob you see.<br /><br />Step Number 5: Once back in PoK, SoW up again and click the Great Divide Book. Head over to Thurgadin and find Erdarf. He is in the bar near the clerics guild. Hand him the Bottle of Karsin Acid and you will receive the Gem of Pursuasion. Suicide on the nearest Dwarf.<br /><br />Step Number 6: Once again re-Sow and click the Great Divide book. Now run over to Kael avoiding every mob you see in the Eastern Wastes. Once in Kael, find the Wolf tamer under the bridge that leads to King Tormax's Throne room. Hand him the Gem of Persuasion you just received from Erdarf. Then re-hand the Giant the Gem he just gave you. Thats right you hand him the gem 2 times. You will now have the Giant Control Harness. Now Suicide on the nearest giant.<br /><br />Step Number 7: Log your Main character on who is probably still in Crystal Caverns. Gate out to PoK. Click the Great Divide book and run over to the Coldain Mines. Re-log your Halfling warrior, get SoW up and return to the Great Divide. Run to the entrance of the Shadow Wurm caves and click an invis potion. There are some Wurms that still see invis so be careful. Hug the left wall until you see the Shardwurm Broodmother. Go to the back of her cave and let the zone know that you are about to initiate the quest. Hopefully no lamers will attack the Broodmother and ruin the quest for you. Hand her the Giant Control Harness and log your Main Character back on.<br /><br />Step Number 8: Once your main character is back on. Get your pet and buffs up. After about 4 mins Korf and his companion will spawn just outside the cave. DO NOT ATTACK HIM YET! Just wait for the Broodmother to arrive, which will be about 8-10mins. As soon and the Broodmother arrives She will attack Korf's companion. As soon as this happens. Korf will de-spawn and a new Korf will pop. This Korf will take off running. Hit him with snare, fear, and your pet will do the rest. He is an easy kill. Loot your new Coldain Military Wristguard and enjoy :)<br /><br /></span></font></td>
              </tr>
